narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: It was mainly a methodology course, so I learned a lot of different tools that could be used to shed light on a sonic phenomenon (voice) that exists, in some fashion, in almost every musical encounter. Voice Studies is also a fairly new field so it was great to learn about very contemporary research, including some work that has not even been published yet. I was drawn primarily to the more philosophical texts and I took away a lot to use in my own interests.
Knowledge about psychoanalytic approaches to voice.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: The readings were all varied, interesting, and come from people of all sorts of academic backgrounds.
